sorting.c
Makefile

How to run and compile:
'make', 'make all', or 'make sorting' will compile the program and all of its required source & header files.
To run the program, type ./sorting.  By default, the program will not sort an array without at least one supplied argument to
specify which sorts to run.

At least one of the following arguments are required to sort an array:
-A: employ all sorting algorithms
-m: enable minSort
-b: enable bubbleSort
-i: enable insertionSort
-q: enable quickSort
-M: enable mergeSort
-u: enable unsorted

The following are optional (but the specified parameter is required):
-p <n>: print the first n elements of the array.  By default, this is 100.
-r <s>: set the random seed to s.  By default, this is 8062022.
-n <c>: set the array size to c.  By default, this is 100.

Description:
This program randomizes an array of size c to 24-bit natural numbers.  Then, determined by the sorting flags set upon runtime,
the array will be sorted by the specified algorithm(s).  The number of element moves and element value comparisons will be
listed above each sort.
